27/05/2003
CAVTAT, Croatia -- The Stability Pact Third Working Table held its seventh regular session in the Adriatic town of Cavtat on Monday (26 May).
According to the foreign ministry, the focus was on progress in security and defence reforms in Southeast Europe.
Participants discussed steps taken since the last session in Romania last June.
Significant results were noted in the development of local democracy, cross-border co-operation, media development, gender equality and issues related to youth and education.
(Vecernji List - 27/05/03;
HINA - 26/05/03)
